- In order to be able to compile programs in Ubuntu you need to have the build-essentials :

sudo apt-get install build-essential

- In order to be able to compile programs in MAC you need to have xcode, xcode terminal programs
and macports

https://developer.apple.com/xcode/

http://www.macports.org/

- To install cmake and boost :

sudo apt-get install libboost-dev cmake (ubuntu)
sudo port install boost cmake (MAC)

- To install findIndexes (path to binaries must be in your PATH variable): 

cd findIndexes
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ../
make
cp findIndexes /path/to/binaries

- To install bowtie2 (not needed in Uppmax) :

cd bowtie2-sources
make
cp bowtie2* /path/to/binaries

- To install Pysam and HTSeq :

sudo apt-get -y install python-dev python-numpy python-matplotlib python-setuptools (Ubuntu)
sudo port install py-numpy py-matplotlib py-setuptools py-pysam (Mac)
sudo easy_install -U pip
sudo easy_install -U cython
sudo easy_install -U distribute
sudo pip install HTSeq 


To install pipeline
cd pipeline
python setup.py build
python setup.py install

If you have problem executing :
export PATH=$PATH:~/path/to/binaries  #findIndexes, bowtie and createDataset.py
export PYTHONPATH=$PATH:~/poath/to/pipeline #path to the python source 

Test by running the command:
      st_pipeline_run.py

     The output it should look like this:

     usage: st_pipeline_run.py [-h] [--output-folder OUTPUT_FOLDER] [--ids IDS]
                          [--ref-map REF_MAP]
                          [--ref-annotation REF_ANNOTATION]
                          [--expName EXPNAME]
                          [--allowed-missed ALLOWED_MISSED]
                          [--allowed-kimer ALLOWED_KIMER]
                          [--min-length-qual-trimming MIN_LENGTH_QUAL_TRIMMING]
                          [--mapping-fw-trimming MAPPING_FW_TRIMMING]
                          [--mapping-rv-trimming MAPPING_RV_TRIMMING]
                          [--length-id LENGTH_ID]
                          [--contaminant-bowtie2-index CONTAMINANT_BOWTIE2_INDEX]
                          [--qual-64] [--htseq-mode HTSEQ_MODE]
                          [--htseq-no-ambiguous] [--start-id START_ID]
                          [--error-id ERROR_ID] [--no-clean-up] [--verbose]
                          [--bowtie-threads BOWTIE_THREADS]
                          [--min-quality-trimming MIN_QUALITY_TRIMMING]
                          [--discard-fw] [--discard-rv] [--bowtie2-discordant]
                          [--bin-path BIN_PATH] [--log-file LOG_FILE]
                          input input
     st_pipeline_run.py: error: too few arguments